abstract_ts:
We have used low‐resolution spectra from the International Ultraviolet Explorer (IUE) to look for periodicities in the ultraviolet flux from α Orionis. The total continuum flux for each observation was integrated, producing longwave (1900–3200 Å) and shortwave (1250–1750 Å) light curves. The periodograms resulting from the shortwave data are noiselike, but the longwave light curves yield statistically significant periods of \documentclass{aastex} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{bm} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{pifont} \usepackage{stmaryrd} \usepackage{textcomp} \usepackage{portland,xspace} \usepackage{amsmath,amsxtra} \usepackage[OT2,OT1]{fontenc} 
